"""Synthetic fixture builder for the hemp decorticator
validation pack (Phase 17.4).

Per spec §12.4, the validation pack is "generated by the
maintainer or the user, not by the platform. For v1, the
pack is synthetic." This script is the synthesizer: it
emits 6 A3-sized PDF fixtures and 6 placeholder sidecar
files for the regression suite
(``tests/test_hemp_decorticator_validation_pack.py``).

The script is **not** called by CI. It is a maintainer
tool. To re-generate the pack after a code change that
affects the validation contract:

    python tests/fixtures/build_synthetic_fixtures.py

**The 6 subsystems** (canonical keys from
``app.vision.machine_graph_builder._SUBSYSTEM_KEYWORDS``):

    hopper, conveyor, compression_rollers, drum, spindle, frame

Each fixture PDF has a hand-typeset title block (with the
machine name, drawing number, revision, material, date),
a BOM line (with the subsystem keyword + a material +
optional mass), and a small set of dimension annotations
(Ø, R, THK, LENGTH). The text is embedded in the PDF
content stream so pdfplumber can extract it on
environments where the library is installed; in
environments without pdfplumber, the chain degrades
gracefully (the orchestrator adapter is mocked in the
regression test, so the absence of OCR is not a
blocker).

**Sidecar contract:**

- ``expected/<name>.graph.json`` — the canonical
  MachineGraph the platform must produce for this
  fixture. The test asserts the platform's actual
  graph is a superset of these nodes (over-extraction
  is allowed; under-extraction fails per spec §5.1).

- ``expected/<name>.score.txt`` — a single float, the
  minimum composite score for a passing run. The
  initial value is the literal string ``TBD`` (the
  maintainer must run the manual reference config
  through the orchestrator, record the composite
  score, and subtract 0.10 per spec §5.1 to get the
  sidecar threshold).

**Why the script computes xref offsets programmatically:**

The hand-stamped xref offsets in
``tests/test_drawing_ingest_e2e.py::MINIMAL_PDF_BYTES``
work for that single fixed-size PDF. This script
synthesizes 6 PDFs with different embedded text
lengths, so the offsets differ per fixture. The
script computes the offsets by walking the object
table once the content stream is built.

**Why no real CAD drawings:**

The spec is explicit (§12.4) that the v1 pack is
synthetic. Real drawings will be added in v1.1+ when
the maintainer has access to client-supplied
fabrication drawings.
"""
from __future__ import annotations

import json
import os
import sys
from pathlib import Path
from typing import Dict, List


